39/*
40 * register definitions for the i82807aa.
41 *
42 * Documentation on this chipset can be found in datasheet #29069001 at
43 * intel.com.
44 */
45
46/*
47 * VCH Revision & GMBus Base Addr
48 */
49#define VR00 0x00
50# define VR00_BASE_ADDRESS_MASK 0x007f
51
52/*
53 * Functionality Enable
54 */
55#define VR01 0x01
56
57/*
58 * Enable the panel fitter
59 */
60# define VR01_PANEL_FIT_ENABLE (1 << 3)
61/*
62 * Enables the LCD display.
63 *
64 * This must not be set while VR01_DVO_BYPASS_ENABLE is set.
65 */
66# define VR01_LCD_ENABLE (1 << 2)
67/** Enables the DVO repeater. */
68# define VR01_DVO_BYPASS_ENABLE (1 << 1)
69/** Enables the DVO clock */
70# define VR01_DVO_ENABLE (1 << 0)
71/** Enable dithering for 18bpp panels. Not documented. */
72# define VR01_DITHER_ENABLE (1 << 4)
73
74/*
75 * LCD Interface Format
76 */
77#define VR10 0x10
78/** Enables LVDS output instead of CMOS */
79# define VR10_LVDS_ENABLE (1 << 4)
80/** Enables 18-bit LVDS output. */
81# define VR10_INTERFACE_1X18 (0 << 2)
82/** Enables 24-bit LVDS or CMOS output */
83# define VR10_INTERFACE_1X24 (1 << 2)
84/** Enables 2x18-bit LVDS or CMOS output. */
85# define VR10_INTERFACE_2X18 (2 << 2)
86/** Enables 2x24-bit LVDS output */
87# define VR10_INTERFACE_2X24 (3 << 2)
88/** Mask that defines the depth of the pipeline */
89# define VR10_INTERFACE_DEPTH_MASK (3 << 2)
90
91/*
92 * VR20 LCD Horizontal Display Size
93 */
94#define VR20 0x20
95
96/*
97 * LCD Vertical Display Size
98 */
99#define VR21 0x21
100
101/*
102 * Panel power down status
103 */
104#define VR30 0x30
105/** Read only bit indicating that the panel is not in a safe poweroff state. */
106# define VR30_PANEL_ON (1 << 15)
107
108#define VR40 0x40
109# define VR40_STALL_ENABLE (1 << 13)
110# define VR40_VERTICAL_INTERP_ENABLE (1 << 12)
111# define VR40_ENHANCED_PANEL_FITTING (1 << 11)
112# define VR40_HORIZONTAL_INTERP_ENABLE (1 << 10)
113# define VR40_AUTO_RATIO_ENABLE (1 << 9)
114# define VR40_CLOCK_GATING_ENABLE (1 << 8)
115
116/*
117 * Panel Fitting Vertical Ratio
118 * (((image_height - 1) << 16) / ((panel_height - 1))) >> 2
119 */
120#define VR41 0x41
121
122/*
123 * Panel Fitting Horizontal Ratio
124 * (((image_width - 1) << 16) / ((panel_width - 1))) >> 2
125 */
126#define VR42 0x42
127
128/*
129 * Horizontal Image Size
130 */
131#define VR43 0x43
132
133/* VR80 GPIO 0
134 */
135#define VR80 0x80
136#define VR81 0x81
137#define VR82 0x82
138#define VR83 0x83
139#define VR84 0x84
140#define VR85 0x85
141#define VR86 0x86
142#define VR87 0x87
143
144/* VR88 GPIO 8
145 */
146#define VR88 0x88
147
148/* Graphics BIOS scratch 0
149 */
150#define VR8E 0x8E
151# define VR8E_PANEL_TYPE_MASK (0xf << 0)
152# define VR8E_PANEL_INTERFACE_CMOS (0 << 4)
153# define VR8E_PANEL_INTERFACE_LVDS (1 << 4)
154# define VR8E_FORCE_DEFAULT_PANEL (1 << 5)
155
156/* Graphics BIOS scratch 1
157 */
158#define VR8F 0x8F
159# define VR8F_VCH_PRESENT (1 << 0)
160# define VR8F_DISPLAY_CONN (1 << 1)
161# define VR8F_POWER_MASK (0x3c)
162# define VR8F_POWER_POS (2)
163
164/* Some Bios implementations do not restore the DVO state upon
165 * resume from standby. Thus, this driver has to handle it
166 * instead. The following list contains all registers that
167 * require saving.
168 */
169static const uint16_t backup_addresses[] = {
170 0x11, 0x12,
171 0x18, 0x19, 0x1a, 0x1f,
172 0x20, 0x21, 0x22, 0x23, 0x24, 0x25, 0x26, 0x27,
173 0x31, 0x32, 0x33, 0x34, 0x35, 0x36, 0x37,
174 0x8e, 0x8f,
175 0x10 /* this must come last */
176};
177
178
179struct ivch_priv {
180 bool quiet;
181
182 uint16_t width, height;
183
184 /* Register backup */
185
186 uint16_t reg_backup[ARRAY_SIZE(backup_addresses)];
187};
188
189
190static void ivch_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo);
191/**
192 * Reads a register on the ivch.
193 *
194 * Each of the 256 registers are 16 bits long.
195 */
196static bool ivch_read(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint16_t *data)
197{
198 struct ivch_priv *priv = dvo->dev_priv;
199 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
200 u8 out_buf[1];
201 u8 in_buf[2];
202
203 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
204 {
205 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
206 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
207 .len = 0,
208 },
209 {
210 .addr = 0,
211 .flags = I2C_M_NOSTART,
212 .len = 1,
213 .buf = out_buf,
214 },
215 {
216 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
217 .flags = I2C_M_RD | I2C_M_NOSTART,
218 .len = 2,
219 .buf = in_buf,
220 }
221 };
222
223 out_buf[0] = addr;
224
225 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, msgs, 3) == 3) {
226 *data = (in_buf[1] << 8) | in_buf[0];
227 return true;
228 }
229
230 if (!priv->quiet) {
231 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to read register 0x%02x from "
232 "%s:%02x.\n",
233 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
234 }
235 return false;
236}
237
238/** Writes a 16-bit register on the ivch */
239static bool ivch_write(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint16_t data)
240{
241 struct ivch_priv *priv = dvo->dev_priv;
242 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
243 u8 out_buf[3];
244 struct i2c_msg msg = {
245 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
246 .flags = 0,
247 .len = 3,
248 .buf = out_buf,
249 };
250
251 out_buf[0] = addr;
252 out_buf[1] = data & 0xff;
253 out_buf[2] = data >> 8;
254
255 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, &msg, 1) == 1)
256 return true;
257
258 if (!priv->quiet) {
259 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to write register 0x%02x to %s:%d.\n",
260 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
261 }
262
263 return false;
264}
265
266/** Probes the given bus and slave address for an ivch */
267static bool ivch_init(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
268 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
269{
270 struct ivch_priv *priv;
271 uint16_t temp;
272 int i;
273
274 priv = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ivch_priv), GFP_KERNEL);
275 if (priv == NULL)
276 return false;
277
278 dvo->i2c_bus = adapter;
279 dvo->dev_priv = priv;
280 priv->quiet = true;
281
282 if (!ivch_read(dvo, VR00, &temp))
283 goto out;
284 priv->quiet = false;
285
286 /* Since the identification bits are probably zeroes, which doesn't seem
287 * very unique, check that the value in the base address field matches
288 * the address it's responding on.
289 */
290 if ((temp & VR00_BASE_ADDRESS_MASK) != dvo->slave_addr) {
291 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ivch detect failed due to address mismatch "
292 "(%d vs %d)\n",
293 (temp & VR00_BASE_ADDRESS_MASK), dvo->slave_addr);
294 goto out;
295 }
296
297 ivch_read(dvo, VR20, &priv->width);
298 ivch_read(dvo, VR21, &priv->height);
299
300 /* Make a backup of the registers to be able to restore them
301 * upon suspend.
302 */
303 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(backup_addresses); i++)
304 ivch_read(dvo, backup_addresses[i], priv->reg_backup + i);
305
306 ivch_dump_regs(dvo);
307
308 return true;
309
310out:
311 kfree(priv);
312 return false;
313}
314
315static enum drm_connector_status ivch_detect(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
316{
317 return connector_status_connected;
318}
319
320static enum drm_mode_status ivch_mode_valid(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
321 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
322{
323 if (mode->clock > 112000)
324 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
325
326 return MODE_OK;
327}
328
329/* Restore the DVO registers after a resume
330 * from RAM. Registers have been saved during
331 * the initialization.
332 */
333static void ivch_reset(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
334{
335 struct ivch_priv *priv = dvo->dev_priv;
336 int i;
337
338 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Resetting the IVCH registers\n");
339
340 ivch_write(dvo, VR10, 0x0000);
341
342 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(backup_addresses); i++)
343 ivch_write(dvo, backup_addresses[i], priv->reg_backup[i]);
344}
345
346/** Sets the power state of the panel connected to the ivch */
347static void ivch_dpms(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, bool enable)
348{
349 int i;
350 uint16_t vr01, vr30, backlight;
351
352 ivch_reset(dvo);
353
354 /* Set the new power state of the panel. */
355 if (!ivch_read(dvo, VR01, &vr01))
356 return;
357
358 if (enable)
359 backlight = 1;
360 else
361 backlight = 0;
362
363 ivch_write(dvo, VR80, backlight);
364
365 if (enable)
366 vr01 |= VR01_LCD_ENABLE | VR01_DVO_ENABLE;
367 else
368 vr01 &= ~(VR01_LCD_ENABLE | VR01_DVO_ENABLE);
369
370 ivch_write(dvo, VR01, vr01);
371
372 /* Wait for the panel to make its state transition */
373 for (i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
374 if (!ivch_read(dvo, VR30, &vr30))
375 break;
376
377 if (((vr30 & VR30_PANEL_ON) != 0) == enable)
378 break;
379 udelay(1000);
380 }
381 /* wait some more; vch may fail to resync sometimes without this */
382 udelay(16 * 1000);
383}
384
385static bool ivch_get_hw_state(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
386{
387 uint16_t vr01;
388
389 ivch_reset(dvo);
390
391 /* Set the new power state of the panel. */
392 if (!ivch_read(dvo, VR01, &vr01))
393 return false;
394
395 if (vr01 & VR01_LCD_ENABLE)
396 return true;
397 else
398 return false;
399}
400
401static void ivch_mode_set(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
402 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
403 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
404{
405 struct ivch_priv *priv = dvo->dev_priv;
406 uint16_t vr40 = 0;
407 uint16_t vr01 = 0;
408 uint16_t vr10;
409
410 ivch_reset(dvo);
411
412 vr10 = priv->reg_backup[ARRAY_SIZE(backup_addresses) - 1];
413
414 /* Enable dithering for 18 bpp pipelines */
415 vr10 &= VR10_INTERFACE_DEPTH_MASK;
416 if (vr10 == VR10_INTERFACE_2X18 || vr10 == VR10_INTERFACE_1X18)
417 vr01 = VR01_DITHER_ENABLE;
418
419 vr40 = (VR40_STALL_ENABLE | VR40_VERTICAL_INTERP_ENABLE |
420 VR40_HORIZONTAL_INTERP_ENABLE);
421
422 if (mode->hdisplay != adjusted_mode->crtc_hdisplay ||
423 mode->vdisplay != adjusted_mode->crtc_vdisplay) {
424 uint16_t x_ratio, y_ratio;
425
426 vr01 |= VR01_PANEL_FIT_ENABLE;
427 vr40 |= VR40_CLOCK_GATING_ENABLE;
428 x_ratio = (((mode->hdisplay - 1) << 16) /
429 (adjusted_mode->crtc_hdisplay - 1)) >> 2;
430 y_ratio = (((mode->vdisplay - 1) << 16) /
431 (adjusted_mode->crtc_vdisplay - 1)) >> 2;
432 ivch_write(dvo, VR42, x_ratio);
433 ivch_write(dvo, VR41, y_ratio);
434 } else {
435 vr01 &= ~VR01_PANEL_FIT_ENABLE;
436 vr40 &= ~VR40_CLOCK_GATING_ENABLE;
437 }
438 vr40 &= ~VR40_AUTO_RATIO_ENABLE;
439
440 ivch_write(dvo, VR01, vr01);
441 ivch_write(dvo, VR40, vr40);
442}
443
444static void ivch_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
445{
446 uint16_t val;
447
448 ivch_read(dvo, VR00, &val);
449 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR00: 0x%04x\n", val);
450 ivch_read(dvo, VR01, &val);
451 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR01: 0x%04x\n", val);
452 ivch_read(dvo, VR10, &val);
453 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR10: 0x%04x\n", val);
454 ivch_read(dvo, VR30, &val);
455 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR30: 0x%04x\n", val);
456 ivch_read(dvo, VR40, &val);
457 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR40: 0x%04x\n", val);
458
459 /* GPIO registers */
460 ivch_read(dvo, VR80, &val);
461 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR80: 0x%04x\n", val);
462 ivch_read(dvo, VR81, &val);
463 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR81: 0x%04x\n", val);
464 ivch_read(dvo, VR82, &val);
465 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR82: 0x%04x\n", val);
466 ivch_read(dvo, VR83, &val);
467 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR83: 0x%04x\n", val);
468 ivch_read(dvo, VR84, &val);
469 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR84: 0x%04x\n", val);
470 ivch_read(dvo, VR85, &val);
471 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR85: 0x%04x\n", val);
472 ivch_read(dvo, VR86, &val);
473 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR86: 0x%04x\n", val);
474 ivch_read(dvo, VR87, &val);
475 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR87: 0x%04x\n", val);
476 ivch_read(dvo, VR88, &val);
477 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR88: 0x%04x\n", val);
478
479 /* Scratch register 0 - AIM Panel type */
480 ivch_read(dvo, VR8E, &val);
481 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR8E: 0x%04x\n", val);
482
483 /* Scratch register 1 - Status register */
484 ivch_read(dvo, VR8F, &val);
485 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VR8F: 0x%04x\n", val);
486}
487
488static void ivch_destroy(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
489{
490 struct ivch_priv *priv = dvo->dev_priv;
491
492 if (priv) {
493 kfree(priv);
494 dvo->dev_priv = NULL;
495 }
496}
497
498struct intel_dvo_dev_ops ivch_ops = {
499 .init = ivch_init,
500 .dpms = ivch_dpms,
501 .get_hw_state = ivch_get_hw_state,
502 .mode_valid = ivch_mode_valid,
503 .mode_set = ivch_mode_set,
504 .detect = ivch_detect,
505 .dump_regs = ivch_dump_regs,
506 .destroy = ivch_destroy,
507};
